{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01RE8apVnBXKebcnpD2o5DVP","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"This is a complex task with specific requirements. Let me break down what I need to do:\n\n1. Generate 100 realistic fake OCR recipe text files\n2. Save to `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.18.txt`\n3. Filenames with SPACES, not hyphens/underscores\n4. Preserve Polish diacritics\n5. Filename must match the main title in the content\n\nRecipe Mix:\n- 60% English, 40% Polish\n- Variety: soups, mains, desserts, salads, appetizers, breads, drinks, preserves\n- Multi-word and single-word titles\n\nOCR Pattern Catalog:\n1. PAGE SPILLOVER (~15%): 10-50 lines of corrupted text from a previous recipe before actual title. File 40-60 lines.\n2. MULTI-LINE SPLIT TITLES (~15%): Title split across 2-4 lines\n3. METADATA PREFIX LINES (~10%): Category or serving info before title\n4. OCR CHARACTER CORRUPTION (~20%): Misrecognized characters throughout\n5. MULTI-LANGUAGE VARIANT TITLES (~5%): Polish line 1, English line 2, etc.\n6. NARRATIVE INTRO (~15%): 3-7 lines of prose between title and ingredients\n7. COMPOUND/COMPLEX TITLES (~5%): Multiple recipes/variations in one title\n8. Simple files (~15%): Basic OCR noise\n\nFile length: 15-60 lines\n\nThis is a substantial generation task. I need to:\n1. Create a systematic approach to generate 100 files\n2. Distribute them across the OCR patterns\n3. Create diverse English and Polish recipes\n4. Write realistic OCR artifacts\n\nLet me think about how to approach this efficiently. I could write a Python script to generate these files, but the user is asking me to generate the files themselves. Given the complexity and volume, I should probably write a Python script that generates all 100 files with the correct patterns and content.\n\n\nActually, I should reconsider whether the user wants me to create the files directly or provide a script. Given the volume and complexity, a script makes more sense. I should check what's already in the directory—looking at the git status, there are many `.generated.18.txt` files already present in `tools/title-loop/input/`, so I'll write a Python script to systematically generate the remaining 100 files with proper distribution across the OCR patterns.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":60876,"cache_read_input_tokens":15568,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":60876},"output_tokens":7,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"6b686ee1-940f-489c-85cf-6ec8e28e5ea8","uuid":"b5f820ef-538f-4374-9dbb-dcd14e846055"}
